olive oil
1 stalk celery
3 clove garlic
1 carrot
1 packet Diced Beef
1 tbs plain flour
1 packet diced bacon
1 tin tinned cherry tomatoes
1 sachet beef-style stock powder
1 tsp brown sugar
1.25 cup water
1 Wholemeal Panini
1 bag parsley
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet Worcestershire sauce
20 g butter (for the sauce)
20 g butter (for the panini)

• Finely chop celery and garlic. Roughly chop carrot.
• In medium bowl, combine diced beef, the plain flour and a pinch of salt and pepper.
• In a large saucepan, heat a generous drizzle of olive oil over high heat. Cook diced beef, turning occasionally, until browned, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a plate.

TIP: If your pan is getting crowded, cook the beef in batches to ensure it browns and doesn't stew.
TIP: The flour will char slightly in the pan, this adds to the flavour!

• Return the saucepan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook diced bacon, carrot and celery, breaking up with a spoon, until golden, 6-7 minutes.
• Add garlic and Aussie spice blend and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.


• Add tinned cherry tomatoes, beef-style stock powder, Worcestershire sauce, the brown sugar, butter (for the sauce) and the water. Return beef to the pan and stir to combine.
• Cover with lid or tightly with foil. Reduce heat to low and simmer until beef is tender, 30-45 minutes. Season to taste.

Little cooks: Kids can help out with measuring the brown sugar and water.

• Cut wholemeal panini into slices. Toast or grill panini to your liking and spread with butter (for the panini).
• Divide one-pot beef, bacon and veggie stew between bowls. Tear over parsley.
• Serve with wholemeal panini. Enjoy!